The paper deals with developing a method for learning interpretable latent structure for images, which involves combining linear independent component analysis (ICA) with non-linear bijective feature maps. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and computer vision, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions achieving better unsupervised latent factor discovery than flow-based models and linear ICA, which suggests that it could also belong to sub-categories related to neural networks and information theory, such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
